### **5.0 Detailed Statistical Analysis**

#### **5.1 Dimensional Score Comparison**

The analysis reveals two fundamentally different civic profiles. McCain's speech is defined by its high scores in civic virtues, whereas Sanders' speech scores highly in both the virtue of Justice and the counter-virtue of Resentment.

| Speaker | Ideology | Dignity | Tribalism | Hope | Resentment | Pragmatism | **Civic Character Index** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
